    <name>
				<text>13.5.3.3 T Integrate Polynomial Fraction</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Evaluate the definite integral \(\displaystyle\int^4_2 {@exp1@} \ \mathrm{d}t =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]].</p>

<p>Note: Please give your answer to 3 decimal places.</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We make use of the fact that \({\displaystyle\int \dfrac{f'(x)}{f(x)}\ \mathrm{d}x} = \ln |f(x)| +c\).</p>
<p>Let \(f(x) = {@f2@}\). Then \(f'(x) = {@f1@}\). Therefore</p>
<p>&nbsp;\(\displaystyle\int^4_2 {@exp1@} \ \mathrm{d}t = \bigg[{@int(exp1,t)@} \bigg]^4_2 = {@int(exp1,t,2,4)@} = {@ta1@}\) to 3 d.p.</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
